Below is a CCEE-oriented MCQ set for Session 1.

üìò Public Key Infrastructure ‚Äì Session 1
Information Security & Security Attacks / Threats
(PG-DITISS August 2025 ‚Äì CCEE Pattern)

‚úÖ 10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced MCQs
Answer key at the bottom.

üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. Information Security primarily ensures:
A. Speed of data
B. Confidentiality, Integrity, Availability
C. Data compression
D. Data redundancy

2. Which is a core principle of Information Security?
A. Authentication
B. Authorization
C. Confidentiality
D. Accounting

3. Confidentiality means:
A. Data is accurate
B. Data is available always
C. Data is accessible only to authorized users
D. Data is backed up

4. Integrity ensures that data is:
A. Hidden
B. Encrypted
C. Not modified without authorization
D. Always accessible

5. Availability ensures:
A. Data secrecy
B. Data correctness
C. Data access when needed
D. Data encryption

6. A security attack is:
A. System failure
B. Any action compromising security
C. Hardware malfunction
D. Power outage

7. Which is a passive attack?
A. Data modification
B. Denial of Service
C. Eavesdropping
D. Spoofing

8. Which is an active attack?
A. Traffic analysis
B. Eavesdropping
C. Masquerading
D. Monitoring

9. Malware includes:
A. Firewall
B. Antivirus
C. Virus
D. Encryption

10. Which attack floods system with requests?
A. Phishing
B. Spoofing
C. DoS
D. Sniffing

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. Which CIA principle is violated by DoS attack?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Authentication

12. Which attack modifies transmitted data?
A. Replay attack
B. Modification attack
C. Traffic analysis
D. Eavesdropping

13. Masquerading attack involves:
A. Monitoring traffic
B. Pretending to be another user
C. Blocking services
D. Destroying data

14. Phishing is best described as:
A. Network attack
B. Social engineering attack
C. Physical attack
D. Cryptographic attack

15. Which threat exploits human behavior?
A. Brute force
B. Phishing
C. Sniffing
D. DoS

16. Which attack records and reuses valid data?
A. Replay attack
B. Trojan horse
C. Worm
D. Spyware

17. Which security service verifies user identity?
A. Authorization
B. Authentication
C. Integrity
D. Availability

18. Trojan horse differs from virus because it:
A. Replicates automatically
B. Requires host program
C. Appears legitimate
D. Attacks hardware

19. Which is NOT malware?
A. Worm
B. Virus
C. Firewall
D. Trojan

20. Passive attacks mainly affect:
A. Integrity
B. Availability
C. Confidentiality
D. Authentication

üî∫ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
21. Traffic analysis is dangerous because:
A. It modifies data
B. It blocks services
C. It reveals communication patterns
D. It destroys systems

22. Which combination is correct?
A. Passive ‚Üí Detection difficult
B. Active ‚Üí No data modification
C. Passive ‚Üí Preventable easily
D. Active ‚Üí No impact

23. Which attack targets system resources?
A. Spoofing
B. DoS
C. Eavesdropping
D. Phishing

24. Integrity attacks include:
A. Traffic analysis
B. Modification
C. Eavesdropping
D. Sniffing

25. Which security goal is MOST affected by replay attack?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. Authentication

26. Which is an example of logical threat?
A. Fire
B. Flood
C. Virus
D. Earthquake

27. Zero-day attack means:
A. No attack
B. Attack on outdated system
C. Attack exploiting unknown vulnerability
D. Attack during system shutdown

28. Which attack uses fake identity and credentials?
A. Sniffing
B. Spoofing
C. DoS
D. Worm

29. Which security mechanism protects against modification?
A. Encryption
B. Hashing
C. Firewall
D. Backup

30. CCEE MOST COMMON TRAP in security is:
A. CIA definitions
B. Passive vs Active attacks
C. Mapping attack to security goal
D. All of the above

‚úÖ ANSWER KEY
Basic:
1.B | 2.C | 3.C | 4.C | 5.C | 6.B | 7.C | 8.C | 9.C | 10.C

Intermediate:
11.C | 12.B | 13.B | 14.B | 15.B | 16.A | 17.B | 18.C | 19.C | 20.C

